	<entry>
		<title>Awake in the Night Land: Grey Dog Interviews John C. Wright</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/235-awake-in-the-night-land-grey-dog-interviews-john-c-wright"/>
		<published>2015-10-25T14:29:53+00:00</published>
		<updated>2015-10-25T14:29:53+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/235-awake-in-the-night-land-grey-dog-interviews-john-c-wright</id>
		<author>
			<name>Kate Coady</name>
			<email>coady.k@protonmail.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;float-left-blog-illo&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/journal-others-illos/awake-in-the-night-land-cover.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;cover of Awake in the Night Land, showing the Last Redoubt&quot; /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://greydogtales.com/blog/?p=436&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Grey Dog Tales has an interview&lt;/a&gt; with author &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scifiwright.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;John C. Wright&lt;/a&gt;, in which they discuss William Hope Hodgson's &lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The Night Land&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The House on the Borderland,&lt;/span&gt; and Mr. Wright's Night Land stories. If you're familiar with this site, you'll know those stories were originally published here by the late &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/107-andy-robertson&quot;&gt;Andy Robertson&lt;/a&gt;. They've since been republished in a collection called &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.castaliahouse.com/downloads/awake-in-the-night-land/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Awake in the Night Land&lt;/a&gt;, published by &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.castaliahouse.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Castalia House&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr. Wright's remarks are well worth the reading, as one might expect.&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;float-left-blog-illo&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/journal-others-illos/awake-in-the-night-land-cover.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;cover of Awake in the Night Land, showing the Last Redoubt&quot; /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://greydogtales.com/blog/?p=436&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Grey Dog Tales has an interview&lt;/a&gt; with author &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scifiwright.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;John C. Wright&lt;/a&gt;, in which they discuss William Hope Hodgson's &lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The Night Land&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&quot;book-title&quot;&gt;The House on the Borderland,&lt;/span&gt; and Mr. Wright's Night Land stories. If you're familiar with this site, you'll know those stories were originally published here by the late &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/107-andy-robertson&quot;&gt;Andy Robertson&lt;/a&gt;. They've since been republished in a collection called &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.castaliahouse.com/downloads/awake-in-the-night-land/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Awake in the Night Land&lt;/a&gt;, published by &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.castaliahouse.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Castalia House&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr. Wright's remarks are well worth the reading, as one might expect.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
